    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-12-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Burnley</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-12-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 31, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your communication of the 6th instant, requesting that the Secretary of the Navy
                    may take into serious consideration the proofs which you offer of the neutrality
                    of the Night Hawk, <pb facs="0112" n="38" xml:id="pg_38"/> and, in reply, to
                    inform you that I have invited his attention to a copy of your note and the
                    original register of the vessel, with the request that he may return the
                    register after having considered its contents.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, the renewed assurance of my high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>J. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hume Burnley,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
